An Act relative to MSBA school funding.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. The school building advisory board established in section 3A of chapter
2 70B of the General Laws shall commission a study of the funding mechanisms for primary,
3 secondary, technical, vocational and agricultural school facilities. The study shall examine the
4 feasibility of creating a funding formula that shall provide increased funding for technical
5 schools where the establishment and maintenance of such school facilities require additional
6 funds that are not necessary for the establishment and maintenance of primary and secondary
7 school facilities.
8 SECTION 2. The school building advisory board shall issue a report, including findings
9 and recommendations on a school facility funding formula that considers the increased costs
10 associated with school facility establishment and maintenance for technical, vocational and
